@Joya 

I liked seeing EARTHA Kitt, too. She was one of the few Western stars to visit Poland in the 1980s. There is a famous picture of her taken at Warsaw's oldest street market - Bazar Różyckiego (yes, we use a Turkish/Persian word to describe a street market - Poland sits at the crossroads between Europe and Asia, and many Asian cultures influenced ours over the centuries. Polish noblemen in the 17th century looked more like Turks than Germans, say).

Here is a link for some pictures of Polish street markets in the 1980s, including the Eartha Kitt one: <a href="https://www.newsweek.pl/historia/bazary-w-prl/eny10xs" target="_blank">https://www.newsweek.pl/historia/bazary-w-prl/eny10xs</a>

